- EXTRA:

To rename filenames matching some criteria:  (remove echo to execute)
find . -type f \( -name "*.cc" -o -name "*.hh" -o -name "*.h"\) -exec bash -c 'echo mv $0 ${0/Name1/Name2}' {} \;

To rename file content for files matching some criteria:
find . -type f \( -name "*.cc" -o -name "*.hh" -o -name "*.h" \) -exec sed -i '' 's/pCT/SomeNewProjName/g' {} \;
